# Profile Page Implementation Specification

**Version:** 1.0
**Date:** 2025-11-17
**Design Reference:** [Figma - Profile Page](https://www.figma.com/design/7BO4GK2CwolnYpcUT28MiT/profile-page?node-id=9-131&t=sVKP7ZMSzTul8JkP-4)

---

## 1. Project Overview

### 1.1 Goals
Build a responsive, accessible profile page that showcases personal information, bio, and technical expertise. This will replace the existing demo application.

### 1.2 Scope
- Single-page profile layout with user card and content sections
- Editable content via TypeScript configuration file
- Responsive design for mobile, tablet, and desktop
- Dark mode support using existing design system
- Interactive elements (social links, tech stack icons)
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)

### 1.3 Design System Reference
From Figma design:
- **Background:** Light beige (#fefdf9)
- **Layout:** Two-column grid (user card left, content right)
- **Typography:** Inter font family
- **Spacing:** Consistent padding and margins
- **Tech Stack Display:** Icon grid with rounded containers

---

## 2. Architecture Decisions

### 2.1 Technology Stack
**No new dependencies required.** Using existing stack:
- **React 19** - UI framework
- **TypeScript** - Type safety and configuration
- **Tailwind CSS v4** - Styling with existing design tokens
- **Shadcn UI** - Button and Card components (already installed)
- **Lucide React** - Icon library (already installed)
- **Bun** - Runtime and bundler

### 2.2 Component Architecture
Following repo best practices:
- Colocate component code with business logic
- Extract reusable utilities to `src/lib/utils.ts`
- Store data configuration in `src/data/` directory
- Keep components in `src/components/` directory

### 2.3 File Structure

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ProfilePage.tsx          # Main page component (replaces App.tsx content)
│   ├── UserCard.tsx             # Left side: avatar, name, title, social links
│   ├── ProfileContent.tsx       # Right side: header and bio content
│   ├── TechStack.tsx            # Bottom: tech stack icon grid
│   └── ui/                      # Existing Shadcn components
│       ├── button.tsx
│       └── card.tsx
├── data/
│   └── profile.config.ts        # Editable profile data (NEW)
├── lib/
│   └── utils.ts                 # Existing utilities (cn, etc.)
├── App.tsx                      # Update to use ProfilePage
└── index.html                   # Existing entry point
public/
└── images/                      # Static assets (NEW)
    ├── avatar.png               # User avatar/profile picture
    └── tech/                    # Tech stack logos
        ├── typescript.png
        ├── react.png
        └── python.png
```

---

## 3. Component Design

### 3.1 ProfilePage Component

**File:** `src/components/ProfilePage.tsx`

**Purpose:** Root layout component that orchestrates the profile page structure.

**Props:** None (uses config file)

**Responsibilities:**
- Import profile data from config
- Render layout grid
- Handle responsive breakpoints
- Apply background styling

**Structure:**
```tsx
import { UserCard } from './UserCard'
import { ProfileContent } from './ProfileContent'
import { TechStack } from './TechStack'
import { profileConfig } from '@/data/profile.config'

export function ProfilePage() {
  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-background">
      <div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[320px_1fr] gap-12">
          <UserCard data={profileConfig.user} />
          <ProfileContent content={profileConfig.content} />
        </div>
        <TechStack technologies={profileConfig.technologies} />
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

---

### 3.2 UserCard Component

**File:** `src/components/UserCard.tsx`

**Purpose:** Display user avatar, name, title, and social links.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface UserCardProps {
  data: {
    avatar: string
    name: string
    title: string
    socialLinks: Array<{
      platform: 'twitter' | 'linkedin' | 'github' | 'email'
      url: string
      ariaLabel: string
    }>
  }
}
```

**Responsibilities:**
- Render Card component with avatar
- Display name and title
- Render social link buttons with icons
- Handle avatar image loading errors
- Provide hover effects on social buttons

**Features:**
- Sticky positioning on desktop (stays visible on scroll)
- Avatar with rounded corners
- Social icons using Lucide React
- Accessible button labels
- Responsive sizing (full width mobile, fixed width desktop)

**Implementation Notes:**
- Use Shadcn Card, CardHeader, CardContent components
- Use Shadcn Button with variant="ghost" for social links
- Icons: `Twitter` (X), `Linkedin`, `Github`, `Mail` from lucide-react
- Avatar fallback: Show initials if image fails to load

---

### 3.3 ProfileContent Component

**File:** `src/components/ProfileContent.tsx`

**Purpose:** Display profile header and bio content.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface ProfileContentProps {
  content: {
    header: string
    subheader: string
    bio: string[]  // Array of paragraphs
  }
}
```

**Responsibilities:**
- Render semantic HTML (h1, p tags)
- Apply proper typography styles
- Handle multiple paragraphs with spacing
- Support markdown-style content (future enhancement)

**Typography Scale:**
- Header: `text-3xl font-bold` (32px from Figma)
- Subheader: `text-lg font-medium` (19px from Figma)
- Body: `text-lg leading-relaxed` (19px from Figma)

**Accessibility:**
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → p)
- Semantic paragraph elements
- Sufficient color contrast

---

### 3.4 TechStack Component

**File:** `src/components/TechStack.tsx`

**Purpose:** Display grid of technology logos with hover effects.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface TechStackProps {
  technologies: Array<{
    name: string
    icon: string
    url?: string
    ariaLabel: string
  }>
}
```

**Responsibilities:**
- Render responsive grid of tech icons
- Apply hover effects (scale, shadow)
- Handle optional links to technology websites
- Provide image alt text and aria labels
- Support keyboard navigation

**Features:**
- Interactive hover effects (scale: 1.05, shadow increase)
- Optional links (clickable if url provided)
- Responsive grid (1 col mobile → 3 cols tablet → 6 cols desktop)
- Focus visible styles for keyboard users
- Image loading error handling (show name text)

**Styling:**
- Icons in rounded containers (112px × 112px from Figma)
- Background: muted color with border
- Smooth transitions on hover
- Grid gap: 24px

---

## 4. Data Management

### 4.1 Profile Configuration File

**File:** `src/data/profile.config.ts`

**Purpose:** Centralized, type-safe configuration for all profile content.

**Structure:**
```typescript
export interface ProfileConfig {
  user: {
    avatar: string
    name: string
    title: string
    socialLinks: Array<{
      platform: 'twitter' | 'linkedin' | 'github' | 'email'
      url: string
      ariaLabel: string
    }>
  }
  content: {
    header: string
    subheader: string
    bio: string[]
  }
  technologies: Array<{
    name: string
    icon: string
    url?: string
    ariaLabel: string
  }>
}

export const profileConfig: ProfileConfig = {
  user: {
    avatar: '/images/avatar.png',
    name: 'Your Name',
    title: 'Your Title',
    socialLinks: [
      {
        platform: 'twitter',
        url: 'https://twitter.com/yourusername',
        ariaLabel: 'Follow on Twitter'
      },
      {
        platform: 'linkedin',
        url: 'https://linkedin.com/in/yourusername',
        ariaLabel: 'Connect on LinkedIn'
      }
    ]
  },
  content: {
    header: 'Header for intro copy',
    subheader: 'Normal font for summary',
    bio: [
      'First paragraph of your bio...',
      'Second paragraph of your bio...'
    ]
  },
  technologies: [
    {
      name: 'TypeScript',
      icon: '/images/tech/typescript.png',
      url: 'https://www.typescriptlang.org/',
      ariaLabel: 'TypeScript - Typed JavaScript at scale'
    },
    {
      name: 'React',
      icon: '/images/tech/react.png',
      url: 'https://react.dev/',
      ariaLabel: 'React - JavaScript library for building user interfaces'
    },
    {
      name: 'Python',
      icon: '/images/tech/python.png',
      url: 'https://www.python.org/',
      ariaLabel: 'Python - Programming language'
    }
  ]
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Single source of truth for content
- Type-safe configuration
- Easy to edit without touching components
- Can be extended to load from JSON/API in future

---

## 5. Styling Strategy

### 5.1 Tailwind CSS Integration

**Approach:** Use Tailwind utility classes with existing design system tokens.

**Existing Tokens (from `styles/globals.css`):**
- `bg-background` - Main background color
- `text-foreground` - Main text color
- `bg-card` - Card backgrounds
- `text-card-foreground` - Card text
- `bg-muted` - Muted backgrounds (for tech icons)
- `text-muted-foreground` - Muted text
- `border` - Border colors

### 5.2 Color Mapping

From Figma design to existing tokens:
- Page background: `bg-background` (already #fefdf9 equivalent)
- Card background: `bg-card`
- Text: `text-foreground`
- Icon containers: `bg-muted`
- Borders: `border`

### 5.3 Responsive Breakpoints

Use Tailwind's default breakpoints:
- **Mobile:** `< 640px` (default, mobile-first)
- **Tablet:** `sm: 640px` and `md: 768px`
- **Desktop:** `lg: 1024px` and `xl: 1280px`

### 5.4 Custom Styles

Minimal custom CSS needed (use Tailwind utilities):
- Hover effects: `hover:scale-105 transition-transform`
- Focus styles: `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring`
- Sticky positioning: `lg:sticky lg:top-8`

---

## 6. Responsive Design

### 6.1 Layout Adaptations

**Mobile (< 1024px):**
```
┌─────────────────────┐
│    User Card        │
│  (Full Width)       │
├─────────────────────┤
│  Profile Content    │
│  (Full Width)       │
├─────────────────────┤
│   Tech Stack        │
│  (2 cols grid)      │
└─────────────────────┘
```

**Desktop (≥ 1024px):**
```
┌──────────┬────────────────────┐
│   User   │                    │
│   Card   │  Profile Content   │
│ (Sticky) │                    │
├──────────┴────────────────────┤
│      Tech Stack                │
│      (Grid 3-6 cols)          │
└───────────────────────────────┘
```

### 6.2 Responsive Classes

**ProfilePage:**
- Container: `container mx-auto px-4 py-8 lg:py-16`
- Grid: `grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[320px_1fr] gap-8 lg:gap-12`

**UserCard:**
- Width: `w-full lg:w-[320px]`
- Sticky: `lg:sticky lg:top-8`
- Avatar size: `w-32 h-32 lg:w-40 lg:h-40`

**TechStack:**
- Grid: `grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-6 gap-6`
- Icon size: `w-20 h-20 lg:w-28 lg:h-28`

### 6.3 Typography Scaling

- Header: `text-2xl lg:text-3xl`
- Subheader: `text-base lg:text-lg`
- Body: `text-base lg:text-lg`

---

## 7. Dark Mode Implementation

### 7.1 Strategy
Leverage existing CSS variables that automatically update with `.dark` class.

**No changes needed to design system.** Existing tokens support dark mode:
- `bg-background` - Auto-adjusts
- `text-foreground` - Auto-adjusts
- `bg-card` - Auto-adjusts
- All other semantic tokens

### 7.2 Component Considerations

**All components automatically support dark mode** through Tailwind classes:
- Use semantic color tokens (not hardcoded colors)
- Example: `bg-card` not `bg-white`
- Example: `text-foreground` not `text-black`

### 7.3 Images in Dark Mode

Tech stack icons may need dark mode variants:
```typescript
// Future enhancement in profile.config.ts
technologies: [
  {
    name: 'TypeScript',
    icon: '/images/tech/typescript.png',
    iconDark: '/images/tech/typescript-dark.png', // Optional
    // ...
  }
]
```

Implementation:
```tsx
<img
  src={icon}
  className="dark:hidden"
  alt={name}
/>
<img
  src={iconDark || icon}
  className="hidden dark:block"
  alt={name}
/>
```

---

## 8. Accessibility Requirements

### 8.1 WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance

**Semantic HTML:**
- Use `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>` landmarks
- Proper heading hierarchy (`<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`)
- Use `<nav>` for navigation elements
- Button elements for interactive items

**Keyboard Navigation:**
- All interactive elements focusable via Tab
- Focus visible styles (ring on focus)
- Logical tab order
- Skip to content link (optional enhancement)

**Screen Reader Support:**
- Meaningful alt text for all images
- ARIA labels for icon-only buttons
- ARIA landmarks for page regions
- Descriptive link text (avoid "click here")

**Color Contrast:**
- Text: Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
- Interactive elements: Minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- Use existing design tokens (already compliant)

### 8.2 Implementation Checklist

**Images:**
```tsx
<img
  src={avatar}
  alt={`${name}'s profile picture`}
  loading="lazy"
/>
```

**Social Links:**
```tsx
<Button
  variant="ghost"
  size="icon"
  asChild
  aria-label={ariaLabel}
>
  <a href={url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
    <Twitter className="h-5 w-5" aria-hidden="true" />
  </a>
</Button>
```

**Tech Stack Icons:**
```tsx
<a
  href={url}
  aria-label={ariaLabel}
  className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring"
>
  <img src={icon} alt="" role="presentation" />
  <span className="sr-only">{name}</span>
</a>
```

### 8.3 Testing Requirements

- Run axe DevTools or similar accessibility scanner
- Test keyboard navigation (Tab, Enter, Escape)
- Test with screen reader (NVDA, JAWS, or VoiceOver)
- Verify color contrast ratios
- Test with browser zoom (200%, 400%)

---

## 9. Interactive Features

### 9.1 Social Links

**Behavior:**
- Open in new tab (`target="_blank"`)
- Security: `rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Hover effect: Background color change
- Active effect: Scale down slightly
- Focus effect: Visible ring

**Icon Mapping:**
```typescript
const iconMap = {
  twitter: Twitter,
  linkedin: Linkedin,
  github: Github,
  email: Mail
}
```

### 9.2 Tech Stack Icons

**Hover Effects:**
```tsx
className={cn(
  "group relative",
  "transition-all duration-300 ease-in-out",
  "hover:scale-105 hover:shadow-lg",
  url && "cursor-pointer"
)}
```

**Features:**
- Scale up 5% on hover
- Add shadow on hover
- Smooth transition (300ms)
- Optional link to technology website
- Tooltip with tech name (future enhancement)

### 9.3 Avatar Image

**Loading States:**
- Use native `loading="lazy"`
- Show initials fallback if image fails
- Smooth fade-in when loaded (optional)

**Implementation:**
```tsx
const [imageError, setImageError] = useState(false)

{imageError ? (
  <div className="flex items-center justify-center bg-muted">
    <span className="text-4xl font-bold">
      {name.split(' ').map(n => n[0]).join('')}
    </span>
  </div>
) : (
  <img
    src={avatar}
    alt={`${name}'s profile picture`}
    onError={() => setImageError(true)}
    loading="lazy"
  />
)}
```

---

## 10. Asset Management

### 10.1 Directory Structure

```
public/
└── images/
    ├── avatar.png              # User profile picture
    └── tech/                   # Technology logos
        ├── typescript.png
        ├── react.png
        ├── python.png
        └── [more as needed]
```

### 10.2 Image Specifications

**Avatar:**
- Format: PNG or WebP
- Size: 320×320px (2x for retina: 640×640px)
- Optimization: Compress to < 100KB
- Accessibility: Meaningful alt text

**Tech Stack Icons:**
- Format: PNG with transparency or SVG
- Size: 112×112px (2x for retina: 224×224px)
- Optimization: Compress to < 50KB each
- Consistency: Same size and style

### 10.3 Optimization Strategy

**Initial Implementation:**
1. Use PNG format for simplicity
2. Manually optimize with tools (TinyPNG, Squoosh)
3. Store in `/public/images/` directory
4. Reference via absolute paths: `/images/avatar.png`

**Future Enhancements:**
- Convert to WebP with PNG fallback
- Implement responsive images (`srcset`)
- Use Bun's asset bundler for optimization
- Consider image CDN for larger deployments

### 10.4 Fallback Strategy

**Missing Images:**
```typescript
// In UserCard component
const [avatarError, setAvatarError] = useState(false)

// In TechStack component
const [iconErrors, setIconErrors] = useState<Record<string, boolean>>({})

// Show initials or placeholder
```

**Loading States:**
```tsx
<img
  src={avatar}
  alt={name}
  loading="lazy"
  className="transition-opacity duration-300"
  onLoad={(e) => e.currentTarget.classList.add('opacity-100')}
  style={{ opacity: 0 }}
/>
```

---

## 11. Error Handling

### 11.1 Image Loading Errors

**Avatar:**
- Fallback to initials display
- Log error to console (dev mode only)
- Maintain layout (no layout shift)

**Tech Icons:**
- Show icon name as text
- Optional: Show placeholder icon
- Graceful degradation

### 11.2 Data Validation

**Config File Validation:**
```typescript
// Add runtime checks in development
if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development') {
  validateProfileConfig(profileConfig)
}

function validateProfileConfig(config: ProfileConfig): void {
  if (!config.user.name) {
    console.warn('Profile config: user.name is required')
  }
  if (!config.user.avatar) {
    console.warn('Profile config: user.avatar is required')
  }
  // ... more validations
}
```

### 11.3 External Link Safety

**All external links:**
- Include `rel="noopener noreferrer"`
- Validate URLs in config (basic check)
- Handle invalid URLs gracefully

**URL Validation:**
```typescript
function isValidUrl(url: string): boolean {
  try {
    new URL(url)
    return true
  } catch {
    return false
  }
}
```

### 11.4 Responsive Behavior

**Container Overflow:**
- Use `overflow-hidden` where appropriate
- Test with very long names/titles
- Implement text truncation if needed

**Grid Layout:**
- Minimum number of tech icons: 1
- Maximum: No hard limit (responsive grid adjusts)
- Test with 0 icons (show message or hide section)

---

## 12. Testing Plan

### 12.1 Unit Tests

**File:** `src/components/__tests__/ProfilePage.test.tsx`

**Framework:** Bun's built-in test runner (`bun test`)

**Test Cases:**

```typescript
import { test, expect } from 'bun:test'
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react'
import { ProfilePage } from '../ProfilePage'

test('renders user name and title', () => {
  render(<ProfilePage />)
  expect(screen.getByText(/Your Name/i)).toBeDefined()
  expect(screen.getByText(/Your Title/i)).toBeDefined()
})

test('renders all social links', () => {
  render(<ProfilePage />)
  const links = screen.getAllByRole('link')
  expect(links.length).toBeGreaterThan(0)
})

test('renders bio content', () => {
  render(<ProfilePage />)
  expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { level: 1 })).toBeDefined()
})

test('renders tech stack icons', () => {
  render(<ProfilePage />)
  const images = screen.getAllByRole('img')
  expect(images.length).toBeGreaterThan(0)
})
```

### 12.2 Component Tests

**UserCard Tests:**
- Renders avatar image
- Shows fallback on image error
- Renders social links with correct URLs
- Links have proper aria-labels
- External links open in new tab

**ProfileContent Tests:**
- Renders header and subheader
- Renders multiple paragraphs
- Maintains proper spacing
- Uses semantic HTML

**TechStack Tests:**
- Renders all technology icons
- Hover effects apply correctly
- Links to tech websites work
- Fallback on missing icons
- Keyboard navigation works

### 12.3 Integration Tests

**Layout Tests:**
- Responsive grid adapts at breakpoints
- Sticky positioning works on desktop
- Mobile layout stacks correctly
- No horizontal overflow at any size

**Accessibility Tests:**
- All images have alt text
- Buttons have aria-labels
- Focus visible on all interactive elements
- Screen reader announces content correctly
- Keyboard navigation follows logical order

**Dark Mode Tests:**
- Colors update correctly
- Images visible in dark mode
- Contrast ratios maintained
- No jarring visual transitions

### 12.4 Visual Regression Tests

**Manual Testing Checklist:**
- [ ] Compare with Figma design at 1920×1080
- [ ] Test at mobile size (375×667)
- [ ] Test at tablet size (768×1024)
- [ ] Test dark mode appearance
- [ ] Test with long content (overflow)
- [ ] Test with missing images
- [ ] Test with different avatar shapes

**Browser Testing:**
- Chrome (latest)
- Firefox (latest)
- Safari (latest)
- Mobile browsers (iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile)

### 12.5 Performance Tests

**Metrics to Monitor:**
- First Contentful Paint (FCP) < 1.5s
- Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) < 2.5s
- Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) < 0.1
- Total page size < 500KB

**Optimization Checks:**
- Images lazy load
- No unnecessary re-renders
- CSS bundle size reasonable
- JavaScript bundle size optimized

