- CMS integration (Sanity, Contentful)

### 15.2 Features

**Interactive:**
- Animated avatar on hover
- Particle background effect
- Scroll animations (fade-in, slide-in)
- Skills progress bars

**Content:**
- Project showcase section
- Experience timeline
- Blog post previews
- Contact form

**Technical:**
- SEO meta tags
- Open Graph images
- RSS feed
- Analytics integration

### 15.3 Performance

- Image CDN integration
- WebP with PNG fallback
- Service worker for offline support
- Critical CSS inlining

---

## 16. Dependencies Justification

**No new dependencies required.**

All features can be implemented with existing stack:

| Feature | Implementation | Existing Dependency |
|---------|---------------|---------------------|
| Icons | Lucide React | `lucide-react` |
| Card UI | Shadcn Card | `@radix-ui/react-*` |
| Buttons | Shadcn Button | `@radix-ui/react-slot` |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS | `tailwindcss` |
| Class Merging | cn() utility | `tailwind-merge`, `clsx` |
| Type Safety | TypeScript | `typescript` |
| Testing | Bun test | Built-in |
| Bundling | Bun bundler | Built-in |

---

## 17. Code Quality Standards

### 17.1 TypeScript

- **No `any` types** (per project rules)
- Use strict mode
- Explicit return types for functions
- Interface over type where possible
- Export types for reusability

### 17.2 React

- Functional components only
- Named exports (not default) for components
- Props interfaces defined inline or exported
- Use `React.ComponentProps` for extending HTML elements
- Proper key props for lists

### 17.3 Styling

- Tailwind utility classes only (no custom CSS)
- Use semantic color tokens (not hardcoded colors)
- Use `cn()` for conditional classes
- Responsive-first approach
- Consistent spacing scale

### 17.4 Accessibility

- Semantic HTML elements
- ARIA labels where needed
- Alt text for all images
- Focus visible styles
- Keyboard navigation support

### 17.5 File Organization

- One component per file
- Colocate related logic
- Extract shared utils to lib/
- Group tests with components
- Clear naming conventions

---

## 18. Risk Mitigation

### 18.1 Potential Issues

**Image Loading:**
- Risk: Images fail to load or are missing
- Mitigation: Implement fallback UI (initials, placeholder text)

**Content Overflow:**
- Risk: Very long names or bios break layout
- Mitigation: Use `overflow-hidden`, `text-ellipsis`, test with edge cases

**Browser Compatibility:**
- Risk: CSS Grid or modern features not supported
- Mitigation: Test in target browsers, use proven patterns

**Performance:**
- Risk: Large images cause slow load times
- Mitigation: Optimize images, lazy loading, monitor bundle size

### 18.2 Rollback Plan

If issues arise:
1. Keep original `App.tsx` backed up
2. Feature flag new ProfilePage
3. Easy to revert to demo app
4. Git history for safe rollback

---

## 19. Success Criteria

### 19.1 Functional Requirements

- [ ] Profile displays all configured content
- [ ] Responsive on mobile, tablet, desktop
- [ ] Social links work and open in new tabs
- [ ] Dark mode works correctly
- [ ] Images load with fallbacks

### 19.2 Non-Functional Requirements

- [ ] Page loads in < 2 seconds
- [ ] No accessibility errors in axe scan
- [ ] No TypeScript errors
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Works in latest Chrome, Firefox, Safari

### 19.3 Design Requirements

- [ ] Matches Figma design
- [ ] Spacing and typography accurate
- [ ] Hover effects smooth and polished
- [ ] Consistent with design system

