## 20. Deployment Notes

### 20.1 Development

```bash
# Install dependencies (if needed)
bun install

# Run dev server with HMR
bun --hot src/index.tsx

# Server runs at http://localhost:3000
```

### 20.2 Production Build

```bash
# Build for production
bun run build.ts

# Output: dist/ directory
# - dist/index.html
# - dist/index.js (bundled)
# - dist/index.css (bundled)
```

### 20.3 Production Server

```bash
# Run production server
NODE_ENV=production bun src/index.tsx

# Or serve static dist/ folder
bun --serve dist/
```

### 20.4 Environment Variables

No environment variables needed for basic implementation.

Optional for future:
- `BUN_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` - Base URL
- `BUN_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID` - Analytics tracking
- `BUN_PUBLIC_API_URL` - API endpoint (future)

---

## Conclusion

This specification provides a complete roadmap for implementing the profile page design. The implementation:

- Uses 100% existing dependencies (no new packages)
- Follows established repo patterns and best practices
- Provides comprehensive accessibility support
- Includes responsive design for all screen sizes
- Supports dark mode out of the box
- Has clear error handling and fallback strategies
- Comes with a complete testing plan
- Can be implemented in approximately 7.5 hours

The developer can begin implementation immediately by following the checklist in Section 13, starting with Phase 1 (Setup and Data) and progressing through each phase sequentially.
